om/gallery/Ap0oPvn</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/akRFJFh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>To those who find it not believable that doctors would have that much trouble figuring out what was wrong consider the following:

Last summer I had a SUPER bad reaction to a new anxiety medication. I soon ended up in the ER with literally debilitating stomach pain and nausea that wouldn't go away. The doctors ran some tests and told me they couldn't see anything wrong, so they billed half of what I earn in a year and sent me home with nothing to treat the symptoms. However, that ER visit was enough to get me pushed to the front of the list with the only gastro specialist in town who would see me and I spent the rest of the year seeing them and other doctors, getting every test under the sun performed on me to figure out what was making me so ill that I ended up having to work from home for quite a while due to not having enough sick days and being too ill to leave the house.

After several months all the doctors and specialists concluded that they had no idea what was making me so ill and could do nothing to help me.

However, a little searching online for information on the drug I had the reaction to revealed reports that the reaction I had was a rare (but documented) possible side effect of the medication. Somehow, despite constantly telling my doctors about this they never even bothered to look into the medication.

I ultimately had to let the problem heal on it's own over the course of half a year.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Ap0oPvn</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Othagovna]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A little watercolor that I made</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Iq22x14</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rrspRxb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Iq22x14</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patricbates]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Getting a pineapple in German supermarket</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/QgsYoFO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/E6lq3gI.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/QgsYoFO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[tampacl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Test 3</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BQS2DFF</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/M3LHBqH.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/BQS2DFF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[martynmagetestaccount]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Memes</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bNfaCuO</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mSAQ7TC.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bNfaCuO</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DOcelot]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Be the hero you were meant to be</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/r83kj5K</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/EH5egpW.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/r83kj5K</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[WeirdAlisMySpiritUserName]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>